HEADWORD: Bignoniaceae
<hw>Bignoniaceae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a natural family comprising the
trees or shrubs or woody vines or herbs having gourdlike or capsular
fruit; the are sometimes placed in the order
<ord>Scrophulariales</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Bignoniaceae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
